The paper focuses on neural architecture search, which is a subfield of machine learning. The proposed method is evaluated on ImageNet, which is a dataset commonly used in computer vision research. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of weight sharing and selective drop mechanisms, which are common techniques in deep learning and neural network optimization, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation and comparison of different network architectures, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
